//purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDas Handbuch behandelt Urbanität als kommunikativ-sprachlich konstituiertes Konzept. Im Zentrum stehen Fragen der systematischen Integration der Urban Linguistics in kanonische Disziplinen der Sprachwissenschaft und die Darstellung von Urbanität als interdisziplinäres Phänomen. Behandelt werden einschlägige Konzepte der internationalen Diskussion sprachbezogener Urban Studies unter konsequentem Bezug auf empirische Daten.  aThis handbook discusses urbanity as a communicative and linguistically constituted concept. Special focus is placed on the integration of urban linguistics into the traditional disciplines of linguistic research and the presentation of urbanity as an interdisciplinary phenomenon. Covering relevant concepts from international research with reference to empirical data, the handbook imparts basic knowledge on a key theme in contemporary linguistics.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aStadtforschung. 4aUrbane Identität. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aUrban Identity.  aUrban Studies.1 aBeal, Joan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBendl, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBritain, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBusse, Beatrix, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBusse, Beatrix, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBär, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBüscher, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCenoz, Jasone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCramer, Jennifer, eco